is commit to Claude Code session context? [Y/n/a]\\n     ```\\n     - **Enter / `y`** → Adds trailer to this commit only. Next commit prompts again.\\n     - **`n`** → No trailer. Commit proceeds without linking.\\n     - **`a`** → Adds trailer AND writes `commit_linking: \\\"always\\\"` to `settings.local.json`. All future commits auto-link without prompting.\\n\\n### On `git commit` (no `-m` flag, editor flow)\\n\\nThe trailer is added as a commented line in the editor. The user can delete it before saving. No interactive prompt — the editor itself is the UI.\\n\\n## State by User Type\\n\\n| User | What happens |\\n|---|---|\\n| Brand new user | Sees `[Y/n/a]` on first `-m` commit with a session. Picks `a` to stop seeing it. |\\n| Existing user (no `commit_linking` set) | Same — sees prompt with new `a` option |\\n| User with `commit_linking: \\\"always\\\"` already | Auto-links silently, unchanged |\\n| User who picks `a` | `settings.local.json` gets the preference (personal, not committed to repo) |\\n\\n## Key Design Points\\n\\n- **`settings.local.json`** is the home for `\\\"always\\\"` — it's a personal preference, not a team setting\\n- **`settings.json` (project)** never gets `commit_linking` written by setup anymore — no more `isFirstSetup` branching or `migrateProjectSettings`\\n- **`GetCommitLinking()`** defaults to `\\\"prompt\\\"` when unset, so the absence of the field is equivalent to explicit `\\\"prompt\\\"`\\n- **Saving is non-fatal** — if `saveCommitLinkingAlways` fails, it logs a warning but the trailer still gets added to the current commit\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":26,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":83631,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":26},\"output_tokens\":14,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYY1iwNLjNRrBjHAjJjsP\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"0cf990